                <head>47. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On February 5, at a closed session of the Twentieth Congress of the Communist
                    Party of the Soviet Union, First Secretary <persName corresp="#p_KNS1">Nikita S.
                        Khrushchev</persName> strongly criticized and condemned <persName>Joseph
                        Stalin</persName> and the cult of personality surrounding him. For
                    documentation on the speech and United States reactions to it, see volume XXIV,
                    pages 72 ff.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
